@* ===========================================================================
   File        : AppHost.razor
   Namespace   : AbsenceApp.Client.Components
   Author      : Michael
   Version     : 2.1.0
   Created     : 2026-03-23
   Updated     : 2026-03-24
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Purpose     : Root Blazor component for the MAUI BlazorWebView.
                 Renders the router directly. Shell chrome (header, sidebar,
                 footer) and auth guard are applied per-page via the layout
                 directives on each page and MainLayout / PageTemplate.
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Notes       :
     - Registered as the RootComponent in MainPage.xaml.
     - Index.razor (route "/") redirects to /login on startup.
     - MainLayout acts as the auth guard for all authenticated pages.
     - PageTemplate provides the full shell (header, sidebar, content, footer).
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Changes     :
     - 1.0.0  2026-03-23  Initial implementation.
     - 2.0.0  2026-03-24  Removed BaseLayoutV2 wrapper. BaseLayoutV2 never
                          rendered ChildContent (only Body), so Routes was
                          silently swallowed: no pages loaded, no auth
                          redirects fired. Routes now renders directly here.
     - 2.1.0  2026-03-24  Added @using AbsenceApp.Client so <Routes /> resolves
                          correctly after namespace separation in V2.
   ===========================================================================
*@
@using AbsenceApp.Client

<!-- =========================================================
     Section: Router host -- all layout/auth handled per-page
     ========================================================= -->
<Routes />